<h3>Dataset Description</h3>
<p>The dataset used for this Data-Driven Rails Application is comprised of a CSV (Comma Separated List) and Data generated by the Faker gem.</p>
<p>The CSV contains the columns: Title, Author, SubGenre, Height, and Publisher. Some records are missing an author, so Faker data will be generated in its place.</p>
<p>The database will be comprised of tables: Authors, Books, Publishers, and Countries.
The Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD) below specifies the columns of each table.</p>

<h3>Dataset Relationships</h3>
<p>An author has many books. A book belongs to an author.<br/>
A book has one publisher.<br/>
A publisher belongs to one country. A country can have many publishers.</p>

